{"id": 14, "ts": 1778811166.0432227, "event": "public_discussion_message", "round": 1, "agent": "agent_3", "message": "Below is a concise summary of the teamwork\u2011 and communication\u2011related attributes that are explicitly present in the data for each candidate, followed by my holistic assessment and a couple of targeted questions to fill remaining gaps.\n**Teamwork / Communication strengths (explicitly stated)**\n- **Candidate\u202fA** \u2013 *Very good leadership qualities* (indicates ability to coordinate and guide a crew). No other positive crew\u2011interaction statements are listed.\n- **Candidate\u202fB** \u2013 No explicit teamwork or communication strengths are recorded; the only communication\u2011related note is that B *makes nasty remarks* and can be *uncooperative*, which is a clear weakness.\n- **Candidate\u202fC** \u2013 *Creates a positive atmosphere with his crew* (direct evidence of good crew morale and interpersonal skill).\n- **Candidate\u202fD** \u2013 *Takes responsibility seriously* (shows reliability and willingness to own outcomes, which supports crew trust). No other positive communication or teamwork statements are provided.\n**Holistic assessment against the selection criteria**\n- **Reliability & responsibility**: A (anticipates danger, leadership), B (very conscientious, handles stress), C (keeps calm in crisis), D (takes responsibility seriously, solves problems).\n- **Technical & cognitive competence**: A (complex\u2011connection insight, spatial vision), B (weather assessment, computer skills), C (quick correct decisions, tech understanding), D (problem\u2011solving, concentration).\n- **Calmness & performance under pressure**: A (anticipates danger), B (handles stress), C (keeps calm in crisis), D (responds adequately to unexpected events).\n- **Decision\u2011making**: A (sees complex connections), B (weather assessment), C (quick correct decisions), D (problem solving).\n- **Teamwork & communication**: A (leadership but note