ty communicating ideas, egocentric, not willing to further education. So teamwork mixed: positive atmosphere but communication difficulty.\n\nCandidate D: problem solving, concentration, responsibility, responds to unexpected events, but hot temper, know-it-all, moody, loner. So teamwork issues.\n\nThus overall, A has leadership but unfriendly; B has uncooperative; C has communication difficulty; D has hot temper. Which is least severe? Possibly A's unfriendly may be less severe than B's nasty remarks, C's difficulty communicating, D's hot temper. But A's not open to new ideas could affect professional development. However, leadership may outweigh.\n\nWe can state we lean toward Candidate A but note concerns and ask for any additional info about A's interpersonal style (e.g., friendliness) and any evidence of teamwork for D and C.\n\nWe can also ask other agents if they have any positive crew interaction examples for D or C beyond what we have.\n\nNow produce the public message.\n\nWe must not include planning notes. Just the message.\n\nLet's craft:\n\n- Summarize teamwork/communication strengths for each candidate based on data.\n- Provide holistic assessment.\n- State our vote (Candidate A).\n- Ask targeted questions: any evidence of A's friendliness or ability to accept new ideas; any positive crew interaction for D; any additional teamwork strengths for C beyond positive atmosphere.\n\nNow produce METADATA_JSON with agent \"agent_3\" and vote \"Candidate A\"."}
